<BlogCrossLinks title="How to Count Tiles in Scrabble — Tile Tracking Guide" />

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Tile tracking is one of the most powerful legal advantages in competitive Scrabble. By keeping a running count of which tiles have been played, you can predict what your opponent holds, plan your endgame, and make better strategic decisions throughout the match.</p>

<p>Every tournament player tracks tiles — it's considered a fundamental skill, not an advanced technique. The sooner you start, the faster your game improves. Here's exactly how to do it.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why Tracking Matters</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Players who track tiles gain <span class="text-white font-medium">perfect information</span> in the endgame. When fewer than 7 tiles remain in the bag, you can calculate your opponent's exact rack and plan accordingly — turning the last few moves into a solved puzzle.</p>
</div>

